knight fellowships reviving environmental journalism knight fellowships reviving environmental journalism training a new generation of science journalists peter lewis 2010 knight fellow hearst visiting professional in residence stanford university lewis came to stanford intending to study business models for new types of journalism instead lewis changed his focus toward one of his journalistic loves science journalism he was struck by the significant decline in top notch science and environmental reporting brought on by years of cuts in us news organizations ultimately he envisioned a program that would train a new generation of science and environmental journalists and also would train scientists how to tell stories to general audiences lewis is continuing to explore various models and options for such a program that would bring the two groups together peter lewis fellowship bio stanford university
